Artist Statement
Perfect Home is about my parents experience living in London, during the July 7th, 2005 bombings in the transit systems. There were a total of four suicide bombings that day, 56 people died, and over 700 people were injured. The exact people responsible for these bombings are unknown, but al-Queda debuty leader Ayman al-Zawahri claimed partial responsibiltiy. Furthermore, it is believed that these people were UK Muslim citizens (grew up in UK, parents are from a majority Muslim country), that became radicalized and learned how to make bombs through the internet.
In panel 1, I drew out security measures taken to defend against bombings. Throughout the 1970s, the IRA (Irish Republican Army) bombed the UK, because they were against the idea of having royalty. The people who were responsible for these bombings wanted to survive, so Transport for London, made their secuity specfically around that. I also drew out the things that the TfL failed to have before the events

I have never lost so hard in my life. Not only my game, but my sanity. The problem with jungling is I can notice everything, every callout or ping, support rotations from the enemy team,  no one listens. Every missed Yone R.  Every strategy the enemy clearly has developed more than us. I can see strengths as Hecarim and Orianna, but mostly weaknesses in our composition. They have Tristana Leona bottom, while we have Bard Jhin. I can see every death, every kill, every outplay, every misplay. And yet I am still lost. We are still lost. We did lose, many times, nearly every time. I hear every squeal of anger, every flaming shot popped. Every obscenity, things that everyone says while playing video games. Lab just could not compete. The level 3 Renekton roam top by Whitney Young. The cheater recall on the third wave in every lane, by Lane. The 0-20 game against Latin, where we tried to do a role swap, and failed miserably. Which reminds me of the forsaken plays we never talk about. Johnny‚Äôs Mundo gank and Seraphine positioning, James‚Äô terrible teleports after the fight was over, Michaels refusal for rotations and dying by not listening, Brandon missing the 5th cannon minion in a row on a mage in mid lane. But I am not clean from fault. 50% of my ganks ended up with both of us dead. I couldn‚Äôt decide on my pathing, red raptors group, or full clear, or five camps, or three.  I didn‚Äôt prioritize the lane with our best player. I saw everything, but not my own mistakes. In a game like League of Legends, you want to blame one person, who solo lost the game, yet you can‚Äôt. We lost, we all contributed to the loss, losing and losing my sanity, while screaming my head off with these teammates was the most fun I have ever had while playing this game.
